<item>
            <title>[CSV-82] CSVRecord inconsistent behaviour when header mapping is not found</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CSV-82</link>
                <project id="12313222" key="CSV">Commons CSV</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CSVRecord#get(String) method has inconsistent behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If no header mapping was provided, then it throws IllegalStateException.&lt;br/&gt;
If the header name is not found, null is returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apart from being inconsistent, it might be useful in the future to be able to return null as a column value (as distinct from the empty string).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should throw IllegalArgumentException for a missing header name, instead of returning null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
